    "body": "May I suggesting expanding on the [brief section](http://docs.cython.org/en/latest/src/userguide/wrapping_CPlusPlus.html#static-member-method) on static member methods?\r\n\r\nThe documentation suggests the following, which is actually incorrect for `shapes::Rectangle::do_something`:\r\n\r\n```cython\r\n# Broken\r\ncdef extern from \"Rectangle.h\" namespace \"shapes\":\r\n    @staticmethod\r\n    void do_something()\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhile it's clear in retrospect that the static method should be attached to the class, historically Cython relied on hacks to access static methods that did go in the outer scope block and these answers are still popular on Stack Overflow. Perhaps it is worth mentioning that the \"Classname::StaticMethod\"() hack is no longer needed here.\r\n\r\nA working example is the following:\r\n\r\n```cython\r\ncdef extern from \"Rectangle.h\" namespace \"shapes\":\r\n    cdef cppclass Rectangle:\r\n        Rectangle() except +\r\n        ...interesting rectangular things...\r\n        @staticmethod\r\n        void do_something()\r\n```",
